b'Qualifications'
b' Ph.D. Electrical and Computer Engineering University of Texas at Austin, 2013'
b' M.S., National Chiao Tung University, Hsinchu, Taiwan, 2006'
b' B.S.,\xc2\xa0National Chiao Tung University, Hsinchu, Taiwan, 2004'
b'Professional Achievments'
b'Dr. Chen has received several prestigious awards, scholarships and national fellowship:'
b' NSF CAREER Award 2018'
b' SPIE Rising Researcher Award 2018'
b' IEEE-APS Raj Mittra Travel Grant (RMTG) Award 2018'
b' WSU College of Engineering Research Excellence Award 2018'
b' IEEE Sensors Council Early Career Award 2017'
b' Young Scientist Award, Union Radio Scientifique Internationale (URSI) 2017'
b' Air Force Research Laboratory Summer Faculty Fellowship 2016'
b' Young Scientist Award, URSI-Commission B: Electromagnetics 2016'
b' Argonne National Laboratory Director\xe2\x80\x99s Fellowship (declined) 2014'
b' University of Texas Professional Development Award 2013'
b' Donald D. Harrington Fellowship 2012'
b' Student Paper Award Finalist, IEEE Antennas and Propagation Symposium \xc2\xa0\xc2\xa0\xc2\xa02011, 2013'
b' Student Paper Award Honorable Mention, IEEE Antennas and Propagation Symposium 2010'
b' Ernest K. Smith Student Award, USNC-URSI National Radio Science Meeting 2012'
b' USNC-URSI Travel Fellowship Awards 2012, 2013'
b' Taiwan Ministry of Education Study Abroad Award 2010'
b' Student Grant of European Physical Society 2010'
b' Honorary Member of Phi Tau Phi Scholastic Honor Society 2006'
b' United Microelectronics Corporation (UMC) Scholarship 2005'
b' Nation Chiao Tung University Presidential Award 2004, 2005'
b'Dr. Chen has supervised graduate students who received awards in major conferences:'
b' Honorable Mention (1 papers), IEEE Antennas and Propagation Symposium 2018'
b' Honorable Mention (2 papers), IEEE Antennas and Propagation Symposium 2017'
b' Student Paper Award Finalist (2 papers), IEEE Antennas and Propagation Symposium 2016'
b' Best Paper Award Finalist, IEEE Sensors Conference 2016'
b' Student Paper Award Finalist, IEEE International Microwave Symposium 2015'
b'Dr. Chen has served as associate editor for IEEE Sensors Journal, IEEE Journal of Electromagnetics, RF and Microwaves in Medicine and Biology (IEEE-JERM), IEEE Journal of Radio Frequency and Identification (IEEE-JRFID), and guest editor for several international journals.'
b'Research Interests'
b'Dr. Chen\xe2\x80\x99s group conducts multidisciplinary research dedicated to applied electromagnetics, wireless microsensors and integrated systems, wireless technologies for RFID, IoT and human-machine interaction applications, as well as electromagnetism at the nanoscale, including plasmonics, meta-materials/surfaces, and nanophotonics.'
b'Publications'
b'Summary: 75 journal papers (including Nature, Nature Electronics, and numerous IEEE transactions), 70 conference papers, one book, six book chapters, and nine US patents\xc2\xa0Statistics (As of Aug. 2018): >2,900 citations, h-index: 27, four journal covers. See the publication details at Google Scholar.'
